    <discussion>Sclerocactus parviflorus has an extensive range and great morphologic variation.
        Many named segregates have been proposed (L. D. Benson 1982; K. D. Heil and J. M. Porter
        1994; F. Hochstätter 1995b) and some of these clearly merit recognition at the subspecific
        or varietal level. However, we are not attempting to subdivide this very complex group.
        Considerable work remains in understanding morphologic diversification within this
        species.</discussion>
